SUMMARY:“London\, Do We Have A Problem?”
LOCATION:London
DESCRIPTION:'London\, do we have a problem?' is the inevitable question tha
 t all residents of the city find themselves asking\, because at this rate\,
  the bad luck feels personal. This comedy-drama play\, based on genuine eve
 nts\, pokes fun at what it means to be a Londoner in 2026\, demonstrating t
 he realities of the student experience (because if we don’t laugh we'll c
 ry). Follow four university students\, who've relocated from opposite ends 
 of the country\, as they navigate living together in The Big Smoke. This br
 and new show is brought to you by Sent West\, a theatre company consisting 
 of four female Drama School Graduates\, slowly but surely completing their 
 mission of correcting the false narrative that ‘women aren’t funny’\,
  following a run of sold-out shows across small venues in London. Join us o
 n this adventure and you’ll either relate\, find solace\, or finally unde
 rstand why our generation is riddled with so much anxiety! It’s just like
  ‘Sex and the City’\, only less chic\, and set during a post-Cov\nMore 
 info: https://comedyatlas.app/comedy-atlas/event/london-do-we-have-a-proble
 m/
